hau, Hai, Leang, Ly, Nhanh, Phan, Pho, Tha.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 歐, meaning ‘to sing someone's praise’ in ancient Chinese: (i) from the placename Dong Ou (東甌), a fief (in present-day Wenzhou in Zhejiang province) which was granted to Yao in 192  BC . It is said that Yao was a descendant of Wujiang (reigned 355–333  BC ), king of the state of Yue (located mainly in present-day Zhejiang and Jiangxi provinces) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (ii) from the placename Ou Yu (歐餘), the name of a fief (located in present-day Zhejiang province) that was granted to Ti, the second son of Wujiang (reigned 355–333  BC ), king of the state of Yue (located mainly in present-day Zhejiang and Jiangxi provinces) during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 區, originally denoting an ancient vessel for measurement in ancient Chinese: from the personal name of <i>Ou Zhizi</i> (歐治子), an expert sword-maker who lived during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). Some of his descendants inherited <i>Ou</i> (歐) as their surname, simplifying the Chinese character 歐 to 區."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice of Jerusalem Princess of Antioch was born in 1110, her father, Baudouin de Jérusalem II,  Roi de Jérusalem, was 32 and her mother, Morfia de Malatya Reine de Jérusalem, was 30. She married Bohemond II de Hauteville Prince of Antioch in 1126. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died after 1151."},"et":{"1110–after 1151":"1110–pärast 1151","1105–1161":"1105–1161","1110–1151":"1110–1151","1110–1164":"1110–1164","1107–1131":"1107–1131","1128–1187":"1128–1187","1078–1131":"1078–1131","1080–1127":"1080–1127","1080":"1080","1 October 1127":"1. oktoober 1127","February 1131":"veebruar 1131","1110":"1110","1187":"1187","1131":"1131","1164":"1164","1151":"1151","1161":"1161","1107":"1107","1128":"1128","1127":"1127","1105":"1105","1126":"1126","about 1128":"umbes 1128","1078":"1078","after 1151":"pärast 1151","21 August 1131":"21. august 1131","Armenia":"Armeenia","Jerusalem, Kingdom of Jerusalem":"Jerusalem, Westjordanland, Palestiina","Antioch, Greece, Europe":"Antiochia","Jerusalem, Kingdom of Jerusalem ":"Jerusalem, Westjordanland, Palestiina"},"fi":{"1110–after 1151":"1110–1151 jälkeen","1105–1161":"1105–1161","1110–1151":"1110–1151","1110–1164":"1110–1164","1107–1131":"1107–1131","1128–1187":"1128–1187","1078–1131":"1078–1131","1080–1127":"1080–1127","1080":"1080","1 October 1127":"1. lokakuuta 1127","February 1131":"helmikuu 1131","1110":"1110","1187":"1187","1131":"1131","1164":"1164","1151":"1151","1161":"1161","1107":"1107","1128":"1128","1127":"1127","1105":"1105","1126":"1126","about 1128":"noin 1128","1078":"1078","after 1151":"1151 jälkeen","21 August 1131":"21. elokuuta 1131","Armenia":"Armenia","Jerusalem, Kingdom of Jerusalem":"Jerusalem, Palestiina, Palestiina","Antioch, Greec